The paper deals with the task of abstractive text summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.AI) fields. The proposed model is based on adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in deep learning (cs.LG) and the paper also mentions the use of neural networks (cs.NE).
